FBIS3-5360 "dreas044_c_94026" FBIS-EAS-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 North Korea Cuban Ambassador, Foreign Visitors Leave Pyongyang SK0503084494 SK0503084494 Article Type:BFN [Editorial Report] Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean at 1300 GMT on 1 March reports on departures of foreign officials who were in Pyongyang. Ho Chong-man, responsible vice chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Koreans Residing in Japan, left Pyongyang on 1 March by plane after visiting the DPRK. Workers Party of Korea Central Committee Secretary Kim Yong-sun and other functionaries concerned bade him farewell at the airport. Juan Jose Leon Vega, Cuban ambassador to the DPRK, returned home on 1 March by plane after being summoned from Cuba. (Jean Carlos Elia Valori), general secretary of the Italian Institute for the Study of International Relations, returned home on 1 March by plane.
